Add support for configuring DNS optional and checking for IoT CatNB mode

This patch set enhances AVC, le_data, le_mrc and cmtool together to support
Legato device deployments in which there is no DNS server provisioned for
resolving server hostnames into IP addresses.

Resolves: LE-14829
Related: LE-12930
Change-Id: Iebcddf972c0cd895fe8eab0b77daf598270566bd

commits.commitMessage:
Update secStore APP path after app/SOTA update

Registered app install/uninstall handlers in secStore service,
the handler will update current APP path, thus when a legato
system is updated by SOTA or app update, current APP path will
be also updated to match current legato index.

Resolves: LE-11686
Related: LEAR7M-487
Change-Id: I22f4144fa268a6dca2975c17c51380ef27a44d8a
Signed-off-by: azhao <azhao@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: Update secStore APP path after app/SOTA update

commits.commitMessage:
New Legato API to terminate the registration (T9/T10)

Add a new API le_ecall_TerminateRegistration(). After ecall normally
ended by PSAP or le_ecall_End(), it's used to terminate registration
state before T9/T10 or NAD_DEREGISTRATION_TIME expired.

Resolves: LE-11483
Related: LEAR7M-470
Change-Id: I6fc73c3dc9b5bc5bf2aef6fa323af189caf00519
Signed-off-by: JuPeng <JuPeng@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: New Legato API to terminate the registration (T9/T10)

commits.commitMessage:
Support multi calls with the same phone number

1: For a given phone number, only one client call object exists at
any time.
2: For a given phone number, More than one non-client call objects
might exist at the same time.
3: Modified GetCallObject(), first get an active call object by call ID,
if fails get an client call object by phone number.
4: Modified NewCallEventHandler(), only update termination reason and
termination code when LE_MCC_EVENT_TERMINATED event is received.
5: Updated mccUnitTest code.

Resolves: LE-12264
Related: LEAR7M-587
Change-Id: Ifebe7b735148fdee9dbe95c4d5ee7342ebc00267
Signed-off-by: azhao <azhao@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: Support multi calls with the same phone number

Replace unsafe strncpy calls by le_utf_Copy

Some calls didn't had the size of the output buffer checked properly
and gcc 8.2 complains about it, and rightfully so.

Resolves: LE-12273

commits.commitMessage:
Add new MRC API to return Global Cell ID

Currently the API returns Physical Cell ID, which is not sufficient
for triangulation.
The fix is to
1) store Global Cell ID in the PCI scan results
2) introduce new API to return Global Cell ID, and update
documentation accordingly
3) update the related test cases.

Resolves: LE-11490
Change-Id: I0fa98c82ab6ce11ad2f3c16153c8a8a868145e05
commits.subject: Add new MRC API to return Global Cell ID

commits.commitMessage:
This is the feature code for DCS refactoring phase 1

This code implements the new le_dcs APIs that support multi data channels and provide
choices over them.  Only cellular is supported in this phase; Wifi & others will be
added thereafter. The le_dcs API implementation has technology-specific code & logic
modularized into its own component & directory.

Resolves: LE-11072 STUDY-1340 LE-8783

commits.commitMessage:
Pass the time/zone/DST information to the OS

Currently, the Linux time is set to UTC, and the time zone
is not changing when the device crosses the timezone boundary.
The fix is:
1) on the modemDaemon startup, query the time/zone information
from the modem
2) pass the time/zone information to the 'tzoneset' utility
3) listen for the timezone update event from the modem, and upon
receiving the event, also pass the information to the
'tzoneset' program.

Resolves: LE-10348
Change-Id: Ie782a8502fbf88cdd98bf68a44789107745ac91c
commits.subject: Pass the time/zone/DST information to the OS

commits.commitMessage:
[eCall] Report system standard change to PA layer

Issue:
When system standard is changed using le_ecall_SetSystemStandard(),
PA layer is not informed and keep using the old system standard.
This causes inconsistency when configuring system standard. (e.g:
PSAP number, eCall timers, ...).

Fix:
Notify PA layer each time system standard changes through
le_ecall_SetSystemStandard() function.

Resolves: LE-10357
Relates: LEAR7M-351
Change-Id: Ieb9a8ef8f96a3aaffadbdc3e7357a3b555fd5f3d
commits.subject: [eCall] Report system standard change to PA layer

After further discussion with Chloe Strainge and Enoch Sun on this issue, it was agreed that the use of LE_ASSERT in the UTF8 library simply follows the original design of the Legato Framework, and should not be considered a bug or deficiency. The use of LE_ASSERT is systemic and has been used throughout Liblegato as a means to catch errors in user-specified parameters. To change this would mean altering the original design and, therefore, would further discussion and study.

It would be better to prefix it with pa_gnssSimu_ in order to indicate that it is a simulation specific function. At least this is what is done in other files around this one.

commits.commitMessage:
Provide default SIM values

Default SIM values have been removed when SIM UTs have been introduced,
so the virtual platform doesn't return any value at the moment leading to
a crash of 'cm sim' for instance.

simuConfig is also provided as a mechanism to set reported values through
the configTree.

Resolves: LE-6857
Change-Id: I9ac51e411d94810032c8e8808b891814ab6af66b
commits.subject: Provide default SIM values

comments.message: I think that the Legato rules require to have a header explaining each static variable. You could at least add a general one on top of this bunch of variables.

Done, although I though you were talking about the APIs at first ... so I updated the APIs as well.
Not sure what the convention is for APIs ... SetSimSomething or SetSIMSomething?

Nothing on https://confluence.sierrawireless.com/display/LEGATO/C+Language (like literally that page doesn't contain much ...)
According to Legato coding rules, this should be on the next line
Why do you need this new function? Can't you just cast a string in pa_sim_CardId_t, which is just an array of chars?
Good call, the only thing it was complaining in the original function was about the const missing.
Maybe add a small header explaining these defines

Maybe could you keep only this function, and only set the parameters which are not empty? In this case, it should be clearly indicated that a NULL parameter is acceptable.

For example pa_simSimu_SetHomeNetworkMcc(mcc); would be replaced by pa_simSimu_SetHomeNetworkMccMnc(mcc, NULL);

The idea to have individual ones is so that the hook from simuConfig (which expects a void (*cb)(const char*) ) can directly take an API without transformation.
I would have add to declare something like the individual ones at some point so I made it public as well.
STK (I think you get it, I won't comment the whole file ;))

Instead of having just a few possibilities here, I think it would be better to have the complete list of SIM states as strings in the function header. This way the user could directly see what values can be used without digging in the code.
Maybe add what is the maximal length of the IMSI in the function header?
Add the acceptable SIM state strings in the header here too
Not necessary if you have the list above
gets (not sure if this should be modified in pa_sim.h too)
Same remark for all the following functions

As you have asserts in these functions, it would be good to add the headers what the maximal length is.

To be done for pa_simSimu_SetHomeNetworkMccMnc, pa_simSimu_SetHomeNetworkMcc, pa_simSimu_SetHomeNetworkMnc
If you are improving this file, it would be good to add a parameter description in all functions, what do you think?

commits.commitMessage:
Provide way to update simu values through ConfigTree

This allows to update values returned by the simu PA
through the ConfigTree.

For instance, to set the PSN, you can do:
 config set /simulation/modem/info/psn TESTPSN

It also makes it possible to handle new values entries
in pa_*_simu.c files and registering this to simuConfig.
The sole use so far is in pa_info_simu.c .

Resolves: LE-6531
Change-Id: Ic23ab3bf9d788bb9a9f7e1f120d7a4ff25286fae
commits.subject: Provide way to update simu values through ConfigTree

Sonar [MAJOR c:FileComplexity]

> File has a complexity of 87 which is greater than 80 authorized.

Variable 'StatusLen' changed to 'RfDeviceStatusLen'.

The api 'le_info_GetRfDeviceStatus()'  returns LE_OVERFLOW if manufacturedIdNumElementsPtr (and remaining NumElementsPtr) is < LE_INFO_RF_DEVICES_STATUS_MAX. If not, then it calls pa_info_GetRfDeviceStatus().
pa_info_GetRfDeviceStatus() checks RfDeviceStatusLen is greater than LE_INFO_RF_DEVICES_STATUS_MAX. If so, it updates the *NumElementsPtr to Zero and returns LE_OVERFLOW. If not, then it assigns RfDeviceStatusLen to *NumElementsPtr and updates the MID , PID and Status fields.

Here, pa_infoSimu_SetRfDeviceStatus() is used to set the values for RfDeviceStatusLen and MID, PID and status with dummy values.
So, This case is not considered.

Meh, you built an API for your UT, I get it, but this file is not just for UTs, so your API is supposed to be generic. A setter that control all values of an array is, IMHO, not very good.
In case you could at least package this in a structure because the current implementation is quite messy.
You need to make sure that len is < LE_INFO_RF_DEVICES_STATUS_MAX or this will overflow.
Could you please update the SIM to INFO, I just noticed that.
